[SN]TITLE[SN]
Rob Evans: Scarlets loose-head prop signs new contract with region

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Scarlets and Wales loose-head prop Rob Evans has signed a new deal keeping him with the west Wales region.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
The 24-year-old came through the Scarlets academy, joining the region at Under-18 level and has gone on to make 81 appearances for the senior side.
"I am really pleased to sign a new deal with the Scarlets," Evans said.
"Playing for the Scarlets is a huge honour. There's a good feeling as we push for silverware and I wanted to be part of that over the next few years."
Evans was part of the Wales U20 team that finished third in the 2012 Junior World Championships in South Africa.
He was so far won 17 senior caps after making his international debut against against Ireland in 2015.
